%% Gambar IV.5 / II.1 - Sequence cache hit dan cache miss
%% Type: Sequence diagram.
%% Reference basis: UML 2.5.1; RFC 9111; Varnish docs.
sequenceDiagram
    actor VU as k6 virtual user
    participant Cache as Varnish cache
    participant Origin as REST/GraphQL origin
    participant DAL as Shared DAL
    participant DB as SQLite corpus

    VU->>Cache: GET cacheable resource
    alt Cache HIT and fresh
        Cache-->>VU: 200 cached response + X-Cache: HIT
    else Cache MISS or stale
        Cache->>Origin: Forward GET request
        Origin->>DAL: read requested resource
        DAL->>DB: SELECT rows
        DB-->>DAL: rows
        DAL-->>Origin: data
        Origin-->>Cache: 200 response + Cache-Control + ETag
        Cache->>Cache: store response if cacheable
        Cache-->>VU: 200 response + X-Cache: MISS
    end

    opt Revalidation after stale response
        Cache->>Origin: GET with If-None-Match
        Origin-->>Cache: 304 Not Modified if ETag matches
        Cache-->>VU: cached body after validation
    end

